    <name>
      <text>Finding Focus and Directrix of a Parabola(Guided)</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Our aim is to find the focus and directrix of the parabola \({@parabola@}\)</p>

<br>

<p>(a) Rewrite the parabola in the form \((x+a)^{2} = c (y+b) \) , where \(a, b\) and \(c\) are constants to be determined.</p>
<p style="margin-left: 30px">[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]</p>
<p>[[feedback:prt1]]</p>

<br>

<p>(b) Recall that, in general, the parabola \((x-x_{0})^{2} = 4 p (y - y_{0}) \) has focus \(F(x_{0}, y_{0}+p)\) and directrix \(y = y_{0}-p\).
<br>Find the focus and directrix of the parabola in part (a).

<p style="margin-left: 30px">Focus: &emsp; \( F \big( \) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] \(,\) [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]]\( \big)\)</p>
<p>[[feedback:prtA]]</p>
<p style="margin-left: 30px">Directrix: &emsp; [[input:ans4]] [[validation:ans4]]</p>
<p>[[feedback:prt4]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked solution</h3>

<p>(a) We are required to rewrite the parabola in the form \((x-a)^2 = c(y-b)\).
<br>To do this, we should "complete the square" with the \(x\) terms and then collect the \(y\) term and constants on the right hand side.</p>
<p style="margin-left: 30px">\(\begin{align*}
{@parabola@} 
&\Rightarrow ({@expr1@}) + ({@expr2@})= 0 \\ 
&\Rightarrow {@(x-aa)^2@} = {@ev(-expr2,simp)@} \\ 
&\Rightarrow {@(x-aa)^2@} = {@4*pp@}({@y-cc@}) 
\end{align*}\)</p>

<br>

<p>(b) We now want to determine the the focus and directrix of this parabola.
<br>Relating the parabola in part (a) to the general form given, we have that,</p>

<p style="margin-left: 30px">\(x_0 = {@aa@}, &emsp; y_0 = {@cc@} &emsp; p = \frac{{@4*pp@}}{4} = {@pp@}\)</p>

<p>Therefore, we can use the general formulae given to find the focus and directrix,</p>
<p style="margin-left: 30px">Focus: &emsp; \( F(x_{0}, y_{0}+p) = ({@aa@},{@cc+pp@}) \)</p>
<p style="margin-left: 30px">Directrix: &emsp; \( y = y_{0}-p = {@cc-pp@} \)</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
